(firstQuint)Efficacy of "Tailored Physical Activity" in Health Care Workers.

 Health care workers have high prevalence of musculoskeletal pain.

 Pain in the back and neck and other musculoskeletal disorders are the leading cause for long-term sick leave.

 This study test the effect of "Tailored Physical Activity" on self-reported days on sick leave and parameters regarding pain, function and quality of life respectively on the body function and participation level of health care workers which have experienced musculoskeletal pain related to the back or upper body.

 A minimum of 44 health care workers in DK-Sonderborg Municipality will be randomized for "Tailored Physical Activity" or a reference group.

 Primary endpoint is 3 months and 12 months follow-up.

